reviewText: Who else could sing others' songs like these two?  Some of the songs on this CD sound better than the originals.  Hall and Oates are SO much better together than apart. If you are a Hall and Oates fan, and have not purchased this newest one, you are missing out.As I am enjoying playing this one in my vehicle's CD player over and over, I await the next one.

reviewText: This is such a great DVD it's hard to know where to begin - the selection of songs, the energy of the band (they are just having a ball and it shows), the rendering and interpretation - it's all just amazing. They didn't take the easy road, these are songs that are really identified with the original artists but Hall and Oates make them their own. Daryl Hall's vocals are soaring and soulful and John Oates is just raw, gritty and great on "What You See Is What You Get". The band is fabulous, so fun to watch. You'll just watch this over and over.
